On this day 43 years ago – apartheid police shot and killed dozens of school children – who were fighting for their right to quality education. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - On this day 43 years ago – apartheid police shot and killed dozens of school children – who were fighting for their right to quality education. June 16 1976 changed South Africa’s socio-political landscape. INFOGRAPHIC: June 16 1976 Every year, June 16th is commemorated – when the youths who lost their lives for freedom are remembered. eNCA reporter Masego Rahlaga takes a look at this day in history in the video above.